> This Mother's Day, serve up a three-course celebratory dinner that will surprise and delight the most important lady in your life (and everyone else at the table). The evening starts with a creamy homemade spinach dip with carrot sticks and tortilla chips, perfect for pairing with mom's fave beverage while you cook. For the main event: juicy seared chicken with a rich cherry pan sauce, tender roasted asparagus, and mashed potatoes loaded with sour cream, Parmesan, scallions, and crisp, smoky bacon. We hope mom's a chocolate-lover, because after dinner, it's rich, fudgy lava cake time! You get the flowers, we've got the rest.

== Loaded Mashed Potatoes ==

Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Place in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Reserve ½ cup potato cooking liquid, then drain.

Return potatoes to pot and mash until smooth and creamy, adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed. Cover to keep warm.

> You'll finish the potatoes in Step 6.

== Cheesy Spinach Dip ==

While potatoes cook, place @spinach{5%ounce} and @water{1%tbsp} in a #large microwave-safe bowl{}. Cover tightly with #plastic wrap{} and microwave until wilted, ~{2-4%minutes}. Carefully remove plastic and transfer spinach to a paper-towel-lined #plate{}; let cool.

> No microwave? No problem! Heat a drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add spinach and cook, stirring, until wilted, 3-4 minutes.

Place @bacon{4%ounce} on a #baking sheet{}; roast on top rack until crispy, ~{15-20%minutes}. Transfer to a #cutting board{}. Once cool enough to handle, roughly chop.

Meanwhile, trim, peel, and cut @carrots{6%ounce} into sticks (like fries; ours were 4 inches long and ½ inch thick). Trim and discard bottom 1 inch from @asparagus{6%ounce}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2%unit}, separating whites from greens.

Once spinach is cool enough to handle, place in the center of a clean #kitchen towel{}. Gather into a tight bundle and squeeze over the sink to remove as much moisture as possible. Finely chop spinach.

Whisk @cream sauce base{4%ounce}, @cheese roux concentrate{1%ounce}, and @garlic powder{1%teaspoon} in a #small pot{} until combined, then set over medium-high heat; cook, whisking, until slightly thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Reduce heat to low; stir in two packets of @sour cream{6%tablespoon} and two packets of @Parmesan cheese{9%tablespoon} until melted and combined, ~{1%minute}. Stir in chopped spinach and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. If mixture seems too thick, stir in a splash of water.

Transfer dip to a #bowl{} and serve with carrot sticks and @blue corn tortilla chips{1.5%ounce} along with Mom's favorite beverage while you prepare the rest of the meal.

> TIP: Prefer to serve the dip with the main course? Reheat over medium-low heat right before serving!

== Cherry Pan Sauce ==

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over high heat. Add chicken and sear until golden brown, ~{2%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer chicken to one side of a second baking sheet. Wipe out pan and let cool slightly.

Toss asparagus on empty side of sheet with a drizzle of oil, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on middle rack until chicken is cooked through and asparagus is tender and lightly browned, ~{10-12%minutes}.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

== Assembly and Serving ==

Stir remaining Parmesan and one packet of sour cream into mashed potatoes until cheese has melted, ~{1%minute}. Fold in half the bacon and half the scallion greens. Taste and season with salt and pepper. Cover to keep warm.

> If bacon isn't finished yet, stir in right before serving.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for chicken over medium heat. Add scallion whites and cook, stirring, until softened and fragrant, ~{1%minute}. Stir in @water{1/4%cup}, @cherry jam{1}, and @chicken stock concentrate{1}. Cook, stirring, until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Remove pan from heat; stir in remaining sour cream and @butter{1%tablespoon}. Season with salt and pepper.

Slice chicken crosswise.

Divide chicken, asparagus, and mashed potatoes between plates. Spoon sauce over chicken and sprinkle potatoes with remaining bacon and remaining scallion greens. Serve.

For dessert, preheat oven to 350 degrees; unwrap thawed @chocolate lava cake{2} and place on a third baking sheet. Heat on middle rack until center is warm and gooey, ~{10-14%minutes}.

> Or microwave for 30-45 seconds for quicker warm-up.

> Bacon is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.